00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:35.808
Okay, first we're going to read Psalm 147.

00:00:36.032 --> 00:00:42.400
Praise the Lord! How good it is to sing praises to our God! How pleasant and fitting to praise Him!

00:00:42.304 --> 00:00:48.864
"The Lord builds up Jerusalem, he gathers the exiles of Israel, he heals the brokenhearted,

00:00:48.608 --> 00:00:51.424
And the binds of their wounds

00:00:51.552 --> 00:00:55.296
He determines the number of stars and calls them each by name.

00:00:55.136 --> 00:01:00.352
Great is our Lord, and mighty in power. His understanding has no limit.

00:01:00.224 --> 00:01:04.352
The Lord sustains the humble, but casts the wicked to the ground.

00:01:04.288 --> 00:01:09.312
Sing to the Lord with grateful praise, making music to our God on the harp.

00:01:09.248 --> 00:01:13.728
He covers the sky with clouds. He supplies the earth with rain.

00:01:13.504 --> 00:01:16.064
And makes grass grow on the hills.

00:01:15.936 --> 00:01:20.320
He provides food to the cattle and for the young ravens when they call

00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:23.296
His pleasure is not in the strength of the horse.

00:01:23.104 --> 00:01:26.240
Nor his delight in the legs of the warrior

00:01:27.584 --> 00:01:29.056
Verse 11

00:01:29.952 --> 00:01:31.872
The lord delights him

00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:35.072
The Lord delights in those who fear Him.

00:01:35.264 --> 00:01:38.880
Who put their hope in his unfailing love

00:01:39.296 --> 00:01:41.952
A soul lord Jerusalem

00:01:42.016 --> 00:01:44.448
Praise your God, Zion!

00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:50.112
He strengthens the bars of your gates and blesses the people within you.

00:01:50.368 --> 00:01:56.064
He grants peace to your barters and satisfies you with the finest of wheat.

00:01:56.928 --> 00:01:59.424
He sends his command to the earth

00:01:59.328 --> 00:02:02.368
With his words run swiftly

00:02:02.624 --> 00:02:08.288
He spreads the snow like wool and scatters the frost like ashes.

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:11.424
He'd hurdles his hair

00:02:11.552 --> 00:02:13.024
Right pebbles

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:16.064
Who can withstand his icy blast?

00:02:16.288 --> 00:02:18.016
He sends his word

00:02:17.888 --> 00:02:19.680
And now it's them.

00:02:19.872 --> 00:02:22.304
He stirs up his breezes

00:02:22.112 --> 00:02:24.160
And the water flows

00:02:24.416 --> 00:02:27.552
He has revealed his word to Jacob.

00:02:27.328 --> 00:02:29.408
The laws and degrees

00:02:29.504 --> 00:02:30.848
of Israel.

00:02:31.136 --> 00:02:35.776
He has done this for no other nation. They do not know his laws.

00:02:35.456 --> 00:02:36.864
Praise the Lord.

00:02:38.624 --> 00:02:44.832
And then we have a question to pros. Come over here, Brett. Let's read the question together. So look at the camera.

00:02:45.408 --> 00:02:46.912
Song

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:49.696
147 questions.

00:02:50.880 --> 00:02:54.944
Has God ever surprised you with a creative

00:02:54.720 --> 00:02:56.224
Alternate

00:02:56.160 --> 00:03:01.216
Alternative alternative to an impossible situation

00:03:01.216 --> 00:03:02.144
Good.

00:03:03.616 --> 00:03:07.872
Is a new creation waiting to be born in your life?

00:03:07.648 --> 00:03:14.464
Now or are you empty and running up against one of your understanding

00:03:14.752 --> 00:03:16.064
And it hurts a lot

00:03:16.032 --> 00:03:19.136
How might God break through through

00:03:18.912 --> 00:03:20.320
Those barriers

00:03:20.864 --> 00:03:23.456
Very good. I'm going to repeat it one more time.

00:03:23.488 --> 00:03:29.216
Has God ever surprised you with a creative alternative to an impossible situation?

00:03:28.992 --> 00:03:36.096
Is a new creation waiting to be born in your life now and are you empty and running up against the limits of your understanding?

00:03:36.864 --> 00:03:39.808
How may God break through those barriers?

00:03:39.584 --> 00:03:41.280
